⏺ Build passes, all 30 tests still green.

  Summary of changes:

  1. App.vue + CompanyFilter.vue — moved company dropdown to the top right of
  the header (with date underneath); rebuilt CompanyFilter with the polished
  styling that previously lived in SummaryCard.
  2. SummaryCard.vue — dropped its own selector and modelValue prop; reads
  selectedCompanyId via inject and shows "Showing {scope}" instead.
  3. NewEntriesTab.vue — today() now returns local YYYY-MM-DD (no UTC midnight
  bug); ⌘D looks at document.activeElement.closest('[data-row]') and duplicates
  the focused row, falling back to the last row if focus is outside the table.
  4. EditEntryModal.vue —
    - Document-level keydown listener with proper Tab/Shift-Tab focus trap
  (cycles between first and last focusable; brings escaped focus back into the
  modal).
    - Esc closes from anywhere in the modal.
    - On open, the first form field gets focus; on close, focus returns to the
  previously active element.
    - role="dialog", aria-modal="true", aria-labelledby.
    - window.confirm replaced with an inline two-step confirmation in the footer
   ("Delete this entry? Cannot be undone." + Cancel / Confirm delete).
  5. EntryRow.vue + EditEntryModal.vue — added request-id guards around every
  async list fetch so stale responses can't overwrite a fresher narrower list.
  6. EntryRow.vue — aria-label on every cell input/select, scoped per row (e.g.
  Company, row 3). Modal selects/inputs got plain field-name aria-labels too.
  7. useCompanyData.js — useCompanies() now returns a module-level singleton
  ref, so SummaryCard / NewEntriesTab / EditEntryModal share the same reactive
  list (network was already deduped; this dedupes the in-memory copies too).
  8. HistoryTab.vue — Edit button is now bg-ink text-paper (always visible,
  inverted), with a focus ring for keyboard users.

