⏺ Done. The modal's employee and project pickers now behave the same as
  EntryRow:

  - On open: the existing employee narrows the project list to projects they're
  on, and the existing project narrows the employee list to people on that
  project.
  - Pick a different employee: projects re-narrow to that employee's projects;
  if the current project isn't on that list, it's cleared (which then refreshes
  the employees to the full company list).
  - Pick a different project: employees re-narrow to people on that project; if
  the current employee isn't on that list, they're cleared.
  - Change company: employee/project/task reset, and both lists fall back to the
   full per-company set.

  All async fetches are wrapped in request-id guards (projectsReqId,
  employeesReqId, companyListsReqId) so a slow earlier response can't overwrite
  a fresher narrower one — same protection EntryRow already had.

