⏺ Done. Behavior now:

  - Global = a specific company (e.g. Company A): every existing row's company
  snaps to A (rows that already had a different company lose their
  employee/project/task — same chain that fires whenever the company changes),
  every new row created via Add row / ⌘B / ⌘D inherits A from blankRow(), and
  the company <select> is :disabled so the user can't change it per-row. The
  placeholder "—" option is hidden when locked, so there's nothing to switch to.
  - Global = All: the lock lifts. Existing rows keep whatever company they had;
  the user can change company freely per row, and new rows start at null (with
  the "—" placeholder back in the dropdown).
  - Switching A → B globally: all rows snap to B; each row's existing
  employee/project/task is cleared by the existing company-change watcher in
  EntryRow.vue (since the values would no longer be valid under B).

